CatDescriptText: Miss Willa Mae Smith, 7144 Vann Drive, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 26, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "In your opinion, what constitutes the 'Leadership' in Negro community in Pittsburgh? What do you think of that which exists?" answer reads: "I think that if given a chance, Negro leaders will prove themselves more worthy.  They could be a lot more aggressive."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Willa Mae Smith wearing patterned head scarf and light colored coat, standing in front of Rosenbaum Company, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
